Package me.opkarol.oppets.pets

Class Pet

java.lang.Object
me.opkarol.oppets.pets.Pet
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Pet extends Object implements Serializable
Pet class is a main serializable public class that is used to create save-able pets objects. It contains all necessary method to manage pet itself. Every method from this class can work as an external API.

  • Constructor Details

    • Pet

      public Pet(String petName, OpPetsEntityTypes.TypeOfEntity petType, UUID ownUUID, UUID ownerUUID, String skillName, boolean active)
      This method is used to create new pet object. Should be only used to generate not value-specific objects. Pet name could= be invalid which will return in a error.
      Parameters:
      petName - name of the pet
      petType - type of the pet
      ownUUID - own uuid of the pet
      ownerUUID - uuid of the owner's pet
      skillName - skill name that pet contains
      active - boolean value - is active

    • Pet

      public Pet(String a, double b1, int b2, OpPetsEntityTypes.TypeOfEntity c, boolean d, UUID e1, UUID e2, String sS, String skill, String prestige)
      This method creates pet entire from scratch. It can be used as an external api connect to create and add own pet objects. All params are focused on pet suitability. This can provide null if params are invalid.
      Parameters:
      a - string pet name
      b1 - double pet experience
      b2 - int level
      c - type
      d - boolean active
      e1 - own uuid
      e2 - owner uuid
      sS - string settings "Serialized as a binary"
      skill - string skill name
      prestige - string prestige combination "level;codes"
